sentences.sContent: She died on June 1, 1968, an outstanding example of the unconquerable human spirit.
sentences.sContent_eng: She died on June 1, 1968, an outstanding example of the unconquerable human spirit.
sentences.sCn: 海伦·凯勒于1968年6月1日与世长辞，她可以说是人类不屈不挠精神的最佳典范。

sentences.sContent: One of those myths, for example, is that Afghanistan is inherently unconquerable thanks to the fierceness of its inhabitants and the formidable nature of its terrain.
sentences.sContent_eng: One of those myths, for example, is that Afghanistan is inherently unconquerable thanks to the fierceness of its inhabitants and the formidable nature of its terrain.
sentences.sCn: 例如，众多谜团之一：由于其原住民的彪悍和其地势的险恶，阿富汗从本质上就是不可征服的。
